@base_url = http://localhost:5097

### 1. Successful Login (Good Input)
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/Login/Login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "admin1",
    "password": "password"
}

### Expected response: 200 OK "Login successful"



### 2. Login with Incorrect Password (Bad Input)
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/Login/Login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "admin",
    "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### Expected response: 401 Unauthorized "Incorrect password"



### 3. Login with Incorrect Username (Bad Input)
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/Login/Login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "wronguser",
    "password": "password123"
}

### Expected response: 401 Unauthorized "Incorrect username"



### 4. Login with Missing Fields (Bad Input)
POST {{base_url}}/api/v1/Login/Login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "",
    "password": ""
}

### Expected response: 400 Bad Request "Username or password is missing"



### 5. Check Admin Login Status when Logged In (Good Input)
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/Login/IsAdminLoggedIn

### Expected response: 200 OK "admin" (or the username stored in the session)



### 6. Check Admin Login Status when Not Logged In (Bad Input)
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/Login/IsAdminLoggedIn

### Expected response: 401 Unauthorized "You are not logged in"



### 7. Logout when Logged In (Good Input)
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/Login/Logout

### Expected response: 200 OK "Logged out"



### 8. Logout when Not Logged In (Bad Input)
GET {{base_url}}/api/v1/Login/Logout

### Expected response: 401 Unauthorized "You are not logged in"
